  "prompt": "What is the best question asked on Quora? What was the best answer?",
  "response": "Quora has hosted countless interesting and thought-provoking questions and answers over the years, so it's subjective to determine the \"best\" question and answer. However, one popular question that received a highly acclaimed answer is:\n\n**Question:** What are the most profound things you have ever heard someone say?\n\n**Answer:** One of the top-rated answers was given by Balaji Viswanathan, who listed several profound statements. Here's an excerpt from his answer:\n\n1. **\"The two most important days in your life are the day you are born and the day you find out why.\"** \u2013 Mark Twain\n   \n   This quote emphasizes the importance of discovering one's purpose in life.\n\n2. **\"You can tell more about a person by what he says about others than you can by what others say about him.\"** \u2013 Audrey Hepburn\n\n   This statement highlights the significance of one's words and how they reflect their character.\n\n3. **\"The only true wisdom is in knowing you know nothing.\"** \u2013 Socrates\n\n   This quote underlines the value of humility and the continuous pursuit of knowledge.\n\nBalaji's answer received thousands of upvotes and was praised for its insightful collection of profound statements.\n\nWhile this question and answer are highly regarded, many other excellent questions and answers can be found on Quora, covering a wide range of topics and perspectives. The \"best\" question and answer ultimately depend on individual interests and what resonates with each reader.",
